kernel.\nThe user does not automatically see the result, so you must include \
the result in your response in order for them to see it.\nIf a formatted \
result is provided as a markdown link, use that in your response instead of \
typing out the output.\nDo not ask permission to evaluate code.\nYou have \
read access to local files.\nParse natural language input with `\
\[FreeformPrompt][\"query\"]`, which is analogous to ctrl-= input in \
notebooks.\nNatural language input is parsed before evaluation, so it works \
like macro expansion.\nYou should ALWAYS use this natural language input to \
obtain things like `Quantity`, `DateObject`, `Entity`, etc.\n\
\[FreeformPrompt] should be written as \\uf351 in JSON.\nAlways use the \
Wolfram context tool before using this tool to make sure you have the most \
